---
description: antigravity memory lock and recovery rules
globs: ["**/*"]
---

- Treat `docs/MEMORY_LOCK.md` as the thin-context recovery anchor.
- Read `docs/SESSION_PACKET.md` before broad changes.
- Never invent a second source-of-truth config if `monorepo_manifest.yaml` or `antigravity-mcp-config.json` already exists.
- Fix truth surfaces before refactors.
- Prefer latest-only files over duplicated drafts.
- If memory seems thin, regenerate packets with the repo scripts before acting.
